SPECIFIC AIMS This proposal will determine, in a rat model of prenatal exposure to ethanol, the alterations in the striatal adenylate cyclase activity during development. The specific aims are: 1) to measure the basal and dopamine stimulated levels of adenylate cyclase activity; 2) to determine and compare the kinetic properties of adenylate cyclase activity in rat striatal membranes; 3) to determine the affinity and density characteristics of the dopamine receptors by binding studies; and 4) to monitor the adenylate cyclase activity of the striatal membranes in the presence of Ca++, calmodulin, GTP, Gpp(NH)p, and DA. 3.
